Description: Wall sherd of East Greek (North Ionian) Late Wild Goat pottery plate; orange clay with white inclusions and some silver mica; glaze fired orange-brown for the most part; exterior: banded decoration; interior: fugitive white slip; in tondo, star of lozenges and buds; outside tondo border, bands; inscription cut on exterior.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 432)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.739)
